{{Use Indian English|date=February 2017}} {{Use dmy dates|date=December 2018}} {{Infobox college |name= St. Bede's College, Shimla |established= 1904 |image=Statue of St. Bede.jpg |caption =Statue of St. Bede at the college |type= Women's | }}
'''St. Bede's College''' is a women's college in [[Shimla]], [[Himachal Pradesh]], [[India]]. The college was originally established as a teacher's training institute in 1904 by the [[Religious of Jesus and Mary]].<ref name=HT>{{cite news|title=Profile: St. Bede’s college, Shimla|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/hteducation/educationnews/profile-st-bede-s-college-shimla/article1-430346.aspx|newspaper=[[Hindustan Times]]|date=9 July 2009|accessdate=5 July 2014 }}</ref><ref name=tribune/>
Today, it offers courses in Economics, English, Geography, Microbiology, etc.<ref name=HT/> and is the only college in [[Himachal Pradesh]] to receive an 'A' accreditation by UGC-NAAC.<ref name=Mingle>{{cite news|title=St. Bede's College, Shimla|url=http://www.minglebox.com/college/St-Bode-s-College-Shimla|website=minglebox|accessdate=5 July 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=History|url=http://www.stbedescollege.in/historyofcollege.htm|accessdate=5 July 2014|publisher=stbedescollege.in }}</ref> Students are commonly known as ''Bedians''.<ref>{{ cite news|title=Ex-Bedians express concern over alma mater|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chandigarh/Ex-Bedians-express-concern-over-alma-mater/articleshow/20838639.cms|newspaper=[[The Times of India]]|date=30 June 2013|accessdate=11 July 2014 }}</ref>
