'''Suzanne Oboler''' is a Peruvian-American scholar, Professor of Latin American and Latina/o Studies at the [[John Jay College of Criminal Justice]] of the [[City University of New York]]. She is the author of ''Ethnic Labels, Latino Lives: Identity and the Politics of (Re)Presentation in the United States'' and the founding Editor of the journal ''Latino Studies'' (2002-2012). She has edited books such as ''Latinos and Citizenship: The Dilemma of Belonging; Behind Bars: Latino/as and Prison in the United States'' (2006) and co-edited ''Neither Enemies nor Friends: Latinos, Blacks, Afro-Latinos'' (2009), and she is co-editor in Chief of ''The Oxford Encyclopedia of Latino/as in the United States''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://johnjayresearch.org/cihr/human-rights-minor/640-2/|title=Suzanne Oboler|publisher=John Jay College of Criminal Justice|accessdate=8 August 2014}}</ref>
